result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

2:30 PM CO: RMW , REP: Melstrom, CLERK: Fox, Defendant Nicole Ann Gans in court, in custody.  Attorney Travis Satorius in court for Nicole Ann Gans. Prosecuting attorney Holly Elkin Rockow in court for the State of Wisconsin. Includes 21CF544, 22CF3 and 22CF366. Atty Satorious recites agreement. Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads GUILTY to Ct 1 - Possession of Meth in 2021CF544 and GUILTY to Ct 3 - Misd criminal damage to property in 2022CF3. DE sworn. Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea. Attorney's stipulate to the facts. Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE guilty of Ct 1 in 2021CF544 and guilty to Ct 3 in 2022CF3. On motion of the State without objection, Crt READS IN and  dismisses Cts 2 and 3 in 2021CF544 and Cts 1 and 2 in 2022CF3 and 2022CF366. Sentencing recommendations. Crt orders:
 
Count 1 - 21CF544: S/W 3 years probation with conditions: 
 - 60 days conditional jail - STAYED, to be used at the discretion of agent.
- $268 Court costs
- $250 DNA surcharge
- DNA sample
- Absolute Sobriety 
- Comply with AODA treatment plan
- Complete any and all programming deemed appropriate by the COMPAS Assessment and by the Department of Corrections. 

Count 3 - 22CF3: S/W 1 year probation with conditions:
- 60 days conditional jail - STAYED, to be used at the discretion of agent.
- $1850 restitution payable to St. Croix County Jail 
- $243 in Court costs 
- $200 in DNA surcharge
- DNA Sample
- Absolute Sobriety 
- Comply with AODA treatment plan
- Complete any and all programming deemed appropriate by the COMPAS Assessment and by the Department of Corrections. 

Credit to be reserved and reviewed in the event of revocation. 
Def advised of right to appeal.
